snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Nin. (And hello to all the system as well!)
I am struggling immensely with a persecutor right now, named Max, who is really ruining some relationships for me. I've seen your video on these kinds of alters, and he is the main trauma holder, I know he is experience tremendous amounts of internal pain and it seems he likes to take the roles of my past abusers and inflict them on me (Eden) like you said so that the abusers themselves don't have to. The main issue I'm having is that often people will call me crazy, or call Max names, once I tell them I have DID and this front is not Eden, that it's an entirely different conscience. He gets very upset when people call him these names, or insult him, and it makes it worse. I have no recollection of what this Alter does while he is fronting, so sometimes when I return to my social medias and such, I see that he has sent messages that obviously I (Eden) would not send, and he is very detrimental to my friendships right now. He is the first Alter I can ever remember being in the headspace, and it almost seems he gets very very upset or angry with me when I grow close to another person. (Outside of the headspace) It's odd because he's my trauma holder but also considers himself a primary protector. He argues with the host, (An alter named Zeeke) and is very very upset with how my system is, well, being a system. What can I do to put him at ease about his concerns about losing me? How do I approach this? I care about him so much, he's the first alter I can remember and he's been here for a few years. I want him to be pleased with me, and with the system, and I want my alters to communicate with him but they're all just irritated with how he acts.


Really hope you see this, I'm not sure who else to go to.


and anyone else who has advice please share!!




Eden

I have no idea why this video was on my recommended list, but I am glad it was.
Let we just say this first; it takes an incredible amount of courage too (for the lack of a better term) expose such a private and personal part of you all to the world in such a public forum, in the hopes to (in my opinion anyway) educate and bring much needed awareness of a very serious condition that is still sadly - not properly understood. We cannot see a breeze, but we accept that it is real...
We cannot see the air we breathe, but we accept that it is real...
We cannot see God, but billions accept that God is real...
I think you get the point....

Yet when it comes to invisible conditions (both physical and psychological) some people (way too many people unfortunately) refuse to accept the existence of DID (for example) simply because they "cannot see it".

The hypocrisy of this fact - will never cease to amaze me. So too them I say this; Either educate yourself or just go away and keep your ignorance to yourself.

After I finished the main presentation, my professor asked “how do you feel about multiple personality disorder?” I had to explain to her that DID had absolutely nothing to do with personality disorders; I found her ignorance concerning and a bit insulting. She had no further questions after that; with other students she would ask multiple questions that required a lot of critical thinking and knowledge on their chosen subject. I absolutely hate when I tell someone that I have BPD and they ask “oh so how many personalities do you have?”. The mixup is so common it hurts. I hope more people watch your videos so that eventually I will no longer have to deal with this ignorance.
